    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and judged acceptable given that (a) ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test condition, (b) the physical bench test is the COU scenario itself with no scenario extrapolation, and (c) the quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three QoIs across all three independent FEA implementations. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the signature workflow is pending and no digital signature is present in this submission.",
